(146, 'Cover-146.jpeg', 'CROSS CULTURE UNDERSTANDING: BRITISH AND AMERICAN', 'Tomi Arianto, S.S., M.A., Afriana, S.S., M.Pd.', '-', 'In this book, the author presented cultural aspects including language, social life, history, politics and law in America and British. The First chapter, the topic discussed about Introduction of English and American studies. In this chapter, student will learn the history of English accents and dialects, especially American English and British English. The second chapter, the topic discussed about Family and Society. In this chapter, student will learn the history of English accents and dialects, especially American English and British English. The third chapter the topic discussed about history. The fourth chapter the topic discussed Politic in US and Britain. In this chapter, student will learn Politics and Politicians, Election in the US, Political Parties in the US, President of the US, Political Parties in Britain, Prime Ministers of Great Britain, and Kings and Queens of England and Great Britain.', 'https://www.instagram.com/p/ClXfwugPu9A/'),
(147, 'Cover-147.jpeg', 'ENGLISH READING PRACTICE', 'Afriana, S.S., M.Pd., Tomi Arianto, S.S., M.A.', '-', 'This book is divided into 12 chapters with each chapter being divided into two parts. The first part has three subdivisions: pre-reading activities, whilst reading activities, and post-reading activities. The pre-reading activities include a vocabulary preview, the most significant determiner in reading comprehension. Following this well-designed pre-reading section is the reading passage and numerous post-reading activities. The post-reading activities focus on recognizing paragraph structure, main ideas, topic sentences, and vocabulary development.', 'https://www.instagram.com/p/ClXhSmwvJ6B/'),
